Description: Fragment of a small seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation and shows darker discolouration. The rear shows a concave surface with a wooden impression like from a bolt, perpendicular to it several impressions of a turned cord with a width of 0.2 cm. The front has a small flat area with downwards bent sides that are partly reshaped and therefore covered with finger prints. On the flat area part of an seal-impression. The same motif is found on EA86891, showing more from the lower part with hieroglyphs: 'Imn and underneath nfr qbH (W15) with water running towards the right and a small circle in the upper part.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
